---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "td"
description: "The td element defines a data cell in a table. Vanilla Breeze styles cells with a thin bottom border and top vertical alignment. Supports data attributes for numeric alignment, custom sort/filter values, and responsive card-mode labels."
elementName: td
category: native
nativeGroup: Tables
currentPath: /docs/elements/native/td/
permalink: /docs/elements/native/td/
---

{% set basicTdCode %}<tbody>
  <tr>
    <td>Wireless Mouse</td>
    <td>Peripherals</td>
    <td>WM-001</td>
    <td data-numeric>245</td>
  </tr>
</tbody>{% endset %}

{% set numericCode %}<td data-numeric>$37,500.00</td>
<td data-numeric>+12.5%</td>
<td data-numeric>1,480</td>{% endset %}

{% set alignCode %}<td data-align="start">Left-aligned text</td>
<td data-align="center">Centered status</td>
<td data-align="end">Right-aligned value</td>{% endset %}

{% set sortValueCode %}<!-- Display shows friendly text, sort uses ISO date -->
<td data-sort-value="2026-03-08">Mar 8, 2026</td>

<!-- Display shows formatted number, sort uses raw value -->
<td data-numeric data-sort-value="37500">$37,500</td>

<!-- Display shows status text, sort uses numeric priority -->
<td data-sort-value="1">Critical</td>{% endset %}

{% set filterValueCode %}<!-- Filter matches on normalized value, not display text -->
<td data-filter-value="electronics peripherals">
  <strong>Wireless Mouse</strong><br />
  <small>Peripherals &middot; Electronics</small>
</td>

<!-- Filter matches alternate spellings or abbreviations -->
<td data-filter-value="united states usa america">
  United States
</td>{% endset %}

{% set dataLabelCode %}<!-- data-label provides column headers in card mode -->
<tr>
  <td data-label="Product">Wireless Mouse</td>
  <td data-label="Category">Peripherals</td>
  <td data-label="SKU">WM-001</td>
  <td data-label="Stock" data-numeric>245</td>
</tr>{% endset %}

{% set headersAttrCode %}<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th id="product">Product</th>
      <th id="q1">Q1</th>
      <th id="q2">Q2</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th id="widget" scope="row">Widget</th>
      <td headers="widget q1">$12,500</td>
      <td headers="widget q2">$15,200</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>{% endset %}

{% set tdCss %}td {
  padding: var(--size-s) var(--size-m);
  border-block-end: var(--border-width-thin) solid
    var(--color-border);
  vertical-align: top;
  text-align: start;
}

/* Numeric alignment */
td[data-numeric] {
  text-align: end;
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
}

/* Explicit alignment */
td[data-align="start"]  { text-align: start; }
td[data-align="center"] { text-align: center; }
td[data-align="end"]    { text-align: end; }

/* Card-mode label (responsive tables) */
td[data-label]::before {
  content: attr(data-label);
  font-weight: 600;
  display: block;
}{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;td&gt;</code> (table data) element contains a cell of data in a table. Data cells are associated with header cells (<a href="/docs/elements/native/th/"><code>&lt;th&gt;</code></a>) through the table structure, primarily via the <code>scope</code> attribute on headers.</p>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze styles data cells with consistent padding (<code>var(--size-s) var(--size-m)</code>), top vertical alignment, and a thin bottom border (<code>var(--border-width-thin)</code>). Row hover effects highlight the entire <a href="/docs/elements/native/tr/"><code>&lt;tr&gt;</code></a> containing the cell.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Data values:</strong> All cells containing actual data (not headers)</li>
      <li><strong>tbody cells:</strong> The primary content within <a href="/docs/elements/native/tbody/"><code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code></a> rows</li>
      <li><strong>tfoot cells:</strong> Summary/total values in <a href="/docs/elements/native/tfoot/"><code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li><strong>Empty cells:</strong> Placeholder cells to maintain column alignment (use "N/A" or "-" rather than leaving blank)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When to Use th Instead</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Column headers:</strong> Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/th/"><code>&lt;th scope="col"&gt;</code></a> in <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li><strong>Row headers:</strong> Use <a href="/docs/elements/native/th/"><code>&lt;th scope="row"&gt;</code></a> when the first cell identifies the row</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Basic Data Cells</h3>
    <p>Data cells contain the values described by column and row headers.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-basic.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/table/basic" title="Basic table with data cells" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic td usage">{{ basicTdCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Numeric Data</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>data-numeric</code> attribute for cells containing numbers. This right-aligns the content and applies <code>font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums</code> so digits align vertically across rows.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Numeric data cells">{{ numericCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Explicit Alignment</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-align</code> when the default (<code>start</code>) or <code>data-numeric</code> (<code>end</code>) are not appropriate for the content.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Explicit alignment">{{ alignCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Custom Sort Values</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-sort-value</code> when the display text differs from the value that should be used for sorting. The <a href="/docs/elements/components/data-table/"><code>&lt;data-table&gt;</code></a> component reads this attribute during sort operations.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Custom sort values">{{ sortValueCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Custom Filter Values</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-filter-value</code> when the cell's display content does not capture all the text a user might search for. The <a href="/docs/elements/components/data-table/"><code>&lt;data-table&gt;</code></a> component uses this for its filter/search feature.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Custom filter values">{{ filterValueCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Responsive Card-Mode Labels</h2>
    <p>On narrow screens, the <a href="/docs/elements/components/data-table/"><code>&lt;data-table&gt;</code></a> component can switch from a traditional table layout to a stacked card layout. Add <code>data-label</code> to each <code>&lt;td&gt;</code> to provide the column header text that appears as a label in card mode.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Card-mode labels">{{ dataLabelCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Complex Header Associations</h2>
    <p>For tables with multiple levels of headers where automatic association via <code>scope</code> is insufficient, use the <code>headers</code> attribute to explicitly list the IDs of the associated header cells.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="headers attribute for complex tables">{{ headersAttrCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>VB Data Attributes</h2>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
