  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Header associations:</strong> Data cells are automatically associated with their column and row headers through the table structure and <code>scope</code></li>
      <li><strong>Screen reader navigation:</strong> When navigating to a <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>, screen readers announce the associated headers</li>
      <li><strong>Complex tables:</strong> Use the <code>headers</code> attribute when automatic association is insufficient</li>
      <li><strong>Avoid empty cells:</strong> Use meaningful placeholders like "N/A" or "-" for better screen reader experience</li>
      <li><strong>Rich content:</strong> When cells contain structured content (links, buttons, status badges), ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
